The B2B air care market can be segmented based on product type, end-user, and distribution channel. In terms of product type, the market includes air fresheners, air sanitizers, and air purifiers. Air fresheners are commonly used in various commercial settings to maintain a pleasant environment, while air sanitizers are crucial in places like hospitals to ensure cleanliness and hygiene. Air purifiers are gaining popularity in office spaces to improve air quality and employee well-being. Regarding end-users, the market caters to hospitals, offices, education institutions, hospitality sectors, and other commercial spaces like industries. Each of these segments has specific air care needs, ranging from odor control to infection prevention. Distribution channels play a vital role in reaching these diverse end-users, with options such as direct sales, distributors, and e-commerce platforms enabling efficient product placement and accessibility.

